                <p>Background noise on iPhone can often disrupt calls and media playback. To reduce this issue, try using noise cancellation settings available in the iPhone. Positioned under accessibility features, they help filter out unwanted sounds. Regular updates might also improve audio performance. Consider using high-quality headphones for better clarity.</p>
